WEBVTT

00:01.101 --> 00:03.436
Previously‐‐
What did you do with Pete?

00:03.504 --> 00:06.471
‐ You killed him.
‐ I hit him, but he fought back.

00:06.540 --> 00:09.876
‐ You murdered him!
‐ We said 50‐50.
We are in this together.

00:09.943 --> 00:11.912
‐ What happened with Pete?
‐ [ Sam ]
Did he take the money?

00:11.978 --> 00:16.216
[ Wayne ] Pete's fine.
Everything's all right.
Pete went home.

00:16.282 --> 00:18.819
Bayou Hills.
It's the deal of a lifetime,
Doug.

00:18.885 --> 00:23.223
It's a hundred
and fifty million,
and you cash in on 13 million.

00:23.289 --> 00:27.794
Doug, this guy named Chet
called for you twice.
He's trying to find Pete Mincey?

00:27.861 --> 00:30.063
Eamon Quinn,
free as a bird.

00:30.130 --> 00:34.000
I just think if we
could do one thing that
we know is true, Wayne.

00:34.067 --> 00:38.505
Dahlia, parole is the tip
of the iceberg here. We do not
want to involve the law.

00:38.572 --> 00:40.741
‐ Parole violator.
‐ I'm honest! I came here
of my own free will.

00:40.807 --> 00:43.176
You can't do this to me.
I just want a chance.

00:43.243 --> 00:48.982
You don't call me in 24 hours
with a job and place to live,
you will be hunted down.

00:49.049 --> 00:52.653
‐ Why are you living in a tent?
‐ He thinks the house
is stealing our souls.

00:52.719 --> 00:56.389
Rather be piss poor with my dad
than $13 million richer
with whoever you are.

00:56.456 --> 00:59.092
‐ I'm not lettin' you leave,
Cael.
‐ Aw, shit, Di. Come on.

00:59.159 --> 01:01.795
I hate good‐byes.

01:05.465 --> 01:08.702
[ Wayne ] He used to do this.
He's done this before.
I mean, it's a weird place.

01:08.769 --> 01:10.837
He hasn't done it
for a while.
No big deal.

01:10.904 --> 01:13.373
<i>[ Dahlia ] You think</i>
<i>I don't know my child?</i>
<i>He always calls.</i>

01:13.439 --> 01:16.042
But you were away for two years,
and while you were away‐‐
<i>[ Thunderclap ]</i>

01:16.109 --> 01:18.311
<i>Don't bring that up.</i>
<i>Don't you dare</i>
<i>bring that up!</i>

01:18.378 --> 01:20.346
It's not about you.
It's about him!

01:20.413 --> 01:22.749
Look, maybe he's with friends.
Maybe he's met a girl.

01:22.816 --> 01:25.586
What girl?
Cael don't like buffer girls.
What girl?

01:25.652 --> 01:27.754
Well, maybe he
met one he likes.

01:27.821 --> 01:31.057
We are his parents, okay?
We're his parents.

01:31.124 --> 01:33.459
We don't know where he is.

01:33.527 --> 01:35.862
Hey, baby.
The thunder wake you?

01:35.929 --> 01:38.264
You woke me up.

01:38.331 --> 01:40.166
[ Ringing ]
Oh, I gotta
take this.

01:40.233 --> 01:41.768
Okay.
Hugh.

01:41.835 --> 01:44.971
‐ Oh, son of a bitch.
‐ No, it's okay. Hugh?

01:45.038 --> 01:47.373
Hugh, calm down.

01:47.440 --> 01:49.543
‐ So‐‐ Oh, don't worry
about it.
‐ Mom?

01:49.610 --> 01:51.177
I will deal with this.
Yeah?

01:51.244 --> 01:53.680
It's gonna be okay.
<i>No, no. Just‐‐</i>

01:53.747 --> 01:56.550
Hugh, are you
listening?
Thanks, baby.

01:56.617 --> 02:00.521
‐ Just calm down. No. It's going
to get‐‐ This is what happens.
‐ <i>[ Line Ringing ]</i>

02:00.587 --> 02:02.823
Oh, Cael, baby.
Please pick up.
This is how it happens.

02:02.889 --> 02:05.458
[ Cell Phone Buzzing ]

02:12.065 --> 02:14.200
[ Thunderclap ]

02:16.970 --> 02:20.440
Just be calm.
You're in control.
Oh, Cael, please pick up, baby.

02:20.507 --> 02:25.378
Are you calm?
Are you sitting down? All right.
Well, sit down somewhere. Okay?

02:25.445 --> 02:27.948
[ Buzzing Continues ]

02:28.014 --> 02:29.883
[ Thunderclaps Continue ]

02:35.922 --> 02:39.626
<i>Just have a‐‐ have a drink.</i>
<i>No, don't have a drink.</i>
<i>No, have a drink.</i>

03:03.249 --> 03:05.251
[ Line Ringing ]

03:57.070 --> 04:00.541
Try calling this morning?
Only about
a couple hundred times.

04:00.607 --> 04:03.243
‐ Yeah, me too.
‐ Dad, I need to talk to you.

04:03.309 --> 04:05.946
‐ Sure, Son. What's it about?
‐ In private.

04:06.012 --> 04:08.281
‐ Hey, can we talk
about it later?
‐ No! It's important.

04:08.348 --> 04:12.352
Yeah, I will talk to you
later tonight, okay?
Now I have to go to work.

04:13.587 --> 04:16.589
Sorry, I didn't get much sleep.

04:18.291 --> 04:20.459
Sammi.

04:21.695 --> 04:25.131
Look, Cael will be okay.
He'll come home.

04:25.198 --> 04:28.935
<i>You know? He'll turn up.</i>
<i>You know he will.</i>
<i>He's a Malloy.</i>

04:29.002 --> 04:31.437
I will get you sooner or later.
I know where you live.

04:31.505 --> 04:34.007
‐ Do you, Wayne?
‐ <i>Am I giving you a lift?</i>

04:34.074 --> 04:36.442
Um, no.
I'm not goin' in today.

04:36.510 --> 04:40.280
Hugh's got me runnin' all over
town. You know, doin' stuff.

04:40.346 --> 04:43.283
‐ Yeah? Doin' what?
‐ Just stuff. You know.

04:43.349 --> 04:46.753
‐ <i>Don't worry about it.</i>
‐ <i>Okay.</i>

04:50.390 --> 04:53.960
‐ [ Line Rings ]
‐ <i>Goddamn it, Cael.</i>

04:54.027 --> 04:56.530
<i>He's not gonna answer, Mom.</i>

04:56.597 --> 04:59.766
How do you know?
'Cause he's gone.

04:59.833 --> 05:02.368
He's on the road.

05:02.435 --> 05:04.805
He tell you that?

05:04.871 --> 05:09.109
‐ In so many words, yeah.
‐ [ Sighing ]

05:09.175 --> 05:11.311
Well, then he's okay.
He's fine.

05:11.377 --> 05:13.379
You know, it's like Dad said.
He's a Malloy.

05:13.446 --> 05:16.349
Why the hell didn't you tell me?
Huh?

05:16.416 --> 05:19.252
I'm goin' out of my mind
all night long!
You didn't think to tell me?

05:19.319 --> 05:21.522
He couldn't take it anymore,
Mom.

05:21.588 --> 05:24.224
‐ You pushed him away.
‐ I did not push him away.

05:24.290 --> 05:28.294
Yes, you did, Mom!
He didn't want to come back,
and you knew it.

05:28.361 --> 05:30.664
That big plan,
he didn't sign up for that.

05:30.731 --> 05:32.533
No.

05:35.569 --> 05:37.671
You're okay though, right?

05:39.339 --> 05:41.942
I'm not Cael.

05:42.008 --> 05:43.944
No.

05:44.911 --> 05:47.413
[ Phone Ringing ]
[ Man Chattering ]

05:47.480 --> 05:50.483
Keep this clean,
be straight with me‐‐

05:50.551 --> 05:53.453
We'll have no problems.
Hmm?

05:53.520 --> 05:56.523
So, you got a place?
Yeah.

05:56.590 --> 05:58.592
And a job?
Yeah.

05:58.659 --> 06:01.394
[ Phone Buzzing ]
Uh‐‐

06:01.461 --> 06:03.630
[ Muttering ]

06:03.697 --> 06:05.298
Shit!

06:05.365 --> 06:08.068
Hell‐‐
[ Sighs ]

06:08.134 --> 06:11.471
Expecting someone?
My son.

06:11.538 --> 06:15.509
He's gone.
Well, his father has him.

06:15.576 --> 06:19.012
Had him.
He's taken off, and‐‐

06:19.079 --> 06:21.982
Ju‐‐
He gonna show up.

06:23.884 --> 06:28.989
I have to, uh, register...
if you're driving.

06:30.356 --> 06:33.126
License and all.

06:33.193 --> 06:35.696
I'm not drivin'.
[ Chuckles ]
I'm takin' the bus.

06:35.762 --> 06:38.331
Mm‐hmm.
I just keep the key
to my first car.

06:38.398 --> 06:42.503
You know, my daddy gave it
to me. He stole it out
of a church parkin' lot.

06:44.070 --> 06:46.840
You know, I should get goin'.
Are we done here?

06:46.907 --> 06:48.875
For now.

06:52.478 --> 06:54.615
[ Bird Cawing ]

07:08.529 --> 07:10.597
[ Sighs ]

07:14.535 --> 07:18.204
Shit.
Where are they?

07:18.271 --> 07:22.676
[ Phone Ringing ]
<i>[ Hugh ] What? What, uh‐‐</i>
<i>Tell him to call me back.</i>

07:22.743 --> 07:26.647
<i>Tell him to call me back!</i>

07:26.713 --> 07:30.050
Damn it.
Morning, Hugh.
Trouble with the phone?

07:30.116 --> 07:32.318
We got a minor problem, Doug‐‐
major minor problem.

07:32.385 --> 07:34.755
Yeah. Minkov.
Ah, Minkov's in the bag.

07:34.821 --> 07:37.624
We need zoning variances for
Bayou Hills, or we're screwed.

07:37.691 --> 07:39.726
Well, let's get
zoning variances then.

07:39.793 --> 07:41.995
They fired Graham.
Great.
Who's Graham?

07:42.062 --> 07:44.865
Graham's the guy at
city hall who took care
of all this crap for me.

07:44.931 --> 07:49.435
He went and got himself mixed up
in the goddamn mayoral scandal,
and now this‐this new guy‐‐

07:49.503 --> 07:51.371
You got the‐‐ Uh‐‐ Yeah.
It's all there.

07:51.437 --> 07:55.375
This new guy has got
a bug up his ass about
doin' things by the book.

07:55.441 --> 07:58.812
[ Scoffs ]
This is Louisiana, Doug!
We don't do things by the book!

07:58.879 --> 08:01.481
Hugh, look.
I mean, there is
no goddamn book!

08:04.751 --> 08:06.787
Look at this junk.
Have you tried
talking to him?

08:06.853 --> 08:10.524
Junk. All junk.
I don't want any of this shit.

08:10.591 --> 08:16.129
He won't return my calls.
Well, then you go down to
city hall and you talk to him.

08:16.196 --> 08:18.965
Doug, it's eerie.
Sometimes you seem to know
what I'm thinkin'...

08:19.032 --> 08:21.267
without me even havin'
a thought in my head.
[ Exhales ]

08:21.334 --> 08:24.671
Come on. Come on.
Weare goin' down
to city hall right now.

08:24.738 --> 08:27.173
Whoa, we?
Mm‐hmm.
People trust you, Doug.

08:27.240 --> 08:30.410
And I know how
to make things happen.
Good cop, bad cop.

08:30.476 --> 08:33.413
I gotta take a piss. Anything
else we need to talk about?
Yes.

08:33.479 --> 08:35.414
Yeah. Quick.
No.

08:35.481 --> 08:37.017
Okay.
All right, piss.

08:37.082 --> 08:41.386
[ Whispers ] Jesus.
Aah! Oh! Jesus H. Christ!
Why would you do that?

08:41.453 --> 08:44.057
Why would you do that?
Don't kick it!

08:44.124 --> 08:46.459
I spent three hours
trying to get this thing
together this morning.

08:46.527 --> 08:49.996
Now I gotta start from scratch.
I have got a lot
on my mind, you know?

08:50.063 --> 08:52.766
Domestic strife?
Is your son still livin'
in the backyard?

08:52.833 --> 08:56.670
Aah! Geez.
My kid is gone, thank you.
[ Quietly ] All right?

08:56.737 --> 08:59.540
[ Phone Rings ]

08:59.606 --> 09:01.775
Uh, Doug Rich?

09:01.842 --> 09:05.045
Um, Chet Landry. Can I have
a moment of your time?

09:05.111 --> 09:10.350
Uh, well, the‐the, uh‐‐
This is not good.

09:10.416 --> 09:12.586
But, Mr. Rich, I'm a‐‐

09:12.653 --> 09:16.322
I'm a private investigator,
and I'm trying to locate
Pete Mincey.

09:17.824 --> 09:20.761
So, uh, Pete's‐‐
Pete's missing?
Well, yeah.

09:20.827 --> 09:25.699
We hope he's just out traveling
or taken an unannounced
vacation. We don't know.

09:25.766 --> 09:30.671
Yeah, this is Dale.
The Malloy kid has hit the road.

09:32.005 --> 09:34.240
Wow, Pete missing.
Well, I‐‐

09:34.307 --> 09:37.110
I wish I could help
you, Mr., uh, Landry.

09:37.177 --> 09:39.746
Uh, please,
call me Chet.
Chet.

09:39.813 --> 09:44.918
Well, I have been
very concerned
about Pete myself.

09:44.985 --> 09:47.888
Eh, well, he was at your house
couple days ago, wasn't he?

09:47.954 --> 09:50.524
The G. P. S. on his rental.

09:50.591 --> 09:52.626
Yes.

09:52.693 --> 09:55.762
This is exactly my point.

09:55.829 --> 09:58.431
Dropping by
to mull over old times.
Hmm.

09:58.498 --> 10:02.302
You know, a surprise visit.
You know how he likes
to pull surprise visits.

10:02.368 --> 10:05.038
[ Chuckles ]
His‐‐ I don't.

10:05.105 --> 10:07.140
Do you remember
what he talked about?

10:07.207 --> 10:10.143
Well, we talked about
the same stories we've
always talked about.

10:10.210 --> 10:13.947
Did he say where he was going
after he saw you?
Uh, going home.

10:14.014 --> 10:19.520
Did he mention seein' a,
uh‐‐ seein' a therapist?

10:19.586 --> 10:22.556
No. He‐He seemed
in very good spirits.

10:22.623 --> 10:24.791
Oh! Is that a fact?

10:24.858 --> 10:29.229
Well, less a fact, Chet,
than an impression.

10:31.331 --> 10:33.233
[ Sighs ]

10:35.201 --> 10:38.772
Thank you for your time.
Thank you.

10:38.839 --> 10:43.109
Hey.
Follow me, follow me.

10:45.045 --> 10:48.649
Do you know who that guy was?
Have you seen him before?
Mm‐mmm.

10:48.715 --> 10:52.018
He's a P. I.
He's looking for Pete.

10:52.085 --> 10:54.588
‐ You didn't say anything,
did you?
‐ Yeah, I told him...

10:54.655 --> 10:57.558
you smashed Pete's skull in
with a hammer and that he's
buried under this old lady.

10:57.624 --> 11:00.961
I'm gonna overlook
that remark for the sake
of our partnership.

11:01.027 --> 11:03.930
Do you want me
to do anything?
I could follow him.

11:03.997 --> 11:07.400
‐ No, no. No, just wait
and see what he does.
‐ All right.

11:11.672 --> 11:14.841
<i>Doug!</i>
<i>You ready?</i>

11:14.908 --> 11:17.678
Yeah, ready as
I'll ever be.
Huh? Let's go.

11:17.744 --> 11:20.480
<i>[ Knocking ]</i>

11:20.547 --> 11:23.283
Hi. Uh, Edenfalls Security.

11:23.349 --> 11:25.251
Yeah.
Uh, something triggered
the alarm up at the guardhouse,

11:25.318 --> 11:27.621
like someone tried to open
a window from the outside...

11:27.688 --> 11:29.222
or the alarm wasn't
deactivated properly.

11:29.289 --> 11:32.125
I should check it out.
Be my guest.

11:32.192 --> 11:37.197
Well, once the alarm's
been activated,
it needs the override, so‐‐

11:37.263 --> 11:40.200
The override?
Yep.
There you go.

11:40.266 --> 11:43.704
Come on. You could have
just told me that...
or called.

11:43.770 --> 11:48.008
Yeah. No, I‐I‐‐
Well, I‐I wanted to
make sure you were okay.

11:48.074 --> 11:50.310
Oh, you wanted
to make sure I was okay?
Well, yeah.

11:50.376 --> 11:53.079
You know, like unharmed
or... whatever.
[ Laughs ]

11:53.146 --> 11:55.415
God, so this is what
you guys do all day?

11:55.481 --> 11:59.285
You just cruise around
Edenfalls? You make sure all
us home‐alone women are okay?

11:59.352 --> 12:01.487
It's my job, ma'am.

12:02.689 --> 12:05.058
Wow.
[ Chuckles ]

12:06.426 --> 12:08.328
Okay, okay. I‐‐

12:09.730 --> 12:11.665
I wanted to see you.

12:11.732 --> 12:13.834
[ Clears Throat ]

12:15.636 --> 12:19.139
[ Laughs ]
Oh, you want to see me?

12:19.205 --> 12:21.274
Oh, no.
No, I‐I didn't, uh‐‐

12:21.341 --> 12:26.680
[ Laughing ] Come on, man.
Lighten up a little bit.
[ Laughs ]

12:26.747 --> 12:30.584
If I were you, I'd want to see
what's goin' on in all these
houses too. You want one?

12:30.651 --> 12:32.986
You ever do that?
Just go in?

12:33.053 --> 12:36.723
You know, check 'em out?
My boss would
have my ass.

12:36.790 --> 12:39.092
Yeah.
Well, you got the keys.

12:43.463 --> 12:48.134
[ Beeping ]
Mmm, n‐n‐no, no, no.
Okay.

12:50.170 --> 12:52.438
Oh, come on.

12:52.506 --> 12:54.374
[ Whispers ]
Wow.

12:55.542 --> 12:58.612
Holy shit.
[ Laughs ]

12:58.679 --> 13:00.547
Why am I whisperin', huh?

13:03.283 --> 13:06.753
‐ [ Dog Yips ]
‐ Hi, puppy.

13:06.820 --> 13:09.289
Oh, uh, don't‐‐
don't get too close.

13:09.355 --> 13:12.092
It's fine. He just wants
a little attention. Huh?
There you go.

13:12.158 --> 13:16.062
‐ What‐What are you doing?
‐ Oh, come on. Relax. He just
wants a little attention.

13:16.129 --> 13:20.000
[ Wayne ] Does the variance
approval process ever move more
rapidly, Commissioner Gilliard?

13:20.066 --> 13:23.970
An application for expedited
processing can be filed
with the mayor's office.

13:24.037 --> 13:26.039
It'll take at least
three months.

13:26.106 --> 13:28.041
Oh, no, no!
Used to take 24 hours.

13:28.108 --> 13:31.377
Yes, well, I'm sure business
will be conducted differently
under the new mayor.

13:31.444 --> 13:34.314
‐ New mayor, meaning‐‐
‐ I don't know, Mr. Rich.

13:34.380 --> 13:37.651
<i>You'll have to ask him.</i>
<i>Or her.</i>

13:37.718 --> 13:42.689
Her?
Carol Phipps. So far
she's the only candidate.

13:42.756 --> 13:45.125
Are you kiddin' me?
You can collect
the paperwork...

13:45.191 --> 13:48.094
for an expedited processing
request at my office...

13:48.161 --> 13:50.897
between 11:45 and 3:15.

13:51.832 --> 13:54.200
Good day, gentlemen.

13:54.267 --> 13:57.037
Good day, you prissy
son of a bitch.

13:57.103 --> 13:59.105
Who's Carol Phipps?
Radical‐‐

13:59.172 --> 14:01.808
Radical environmentalist.
Dangerous.

14:01.875 --> 14:05.879
Dangerous ecoterrorist.
Ran a "save the swamp flea"
campaign up in Lafayette.

14:05.946 --> 14:08.081
Shut down an arena project
I had goin' in.

14:08.148 --> 14:11.084
Now she's gonna
come after Bayou Hills.

14:11.151 --> 14:14.688
We could do something
about that.
Yeah, what's that?

14:14.755 --> 14:19.993
You're gonna run for mayor.
[ Laughs ] I don't have
time for that shit.

14:20.060 --> 14:22.128
<i>Oh, no, don't‐‐</i>
<i>Oh, my God.</i>

14:22.195 --> 14:24.097
Ooh. Oh, ma‐‐
[ Gags ]
[ Di Di Laughs ]

14:24.164 --> 14:26.266
Oh, my God!
He shat.

14:26.332 --> 14:29.435
Ooh.
Oh, why did you do that?

14:29.503 --> 14:31.638
‐ That's great.
‐ No, that is not great.

14:31.705 --> 14:33.874
‐ Oh, come on.
‐ Here, we have
to clean that up.

14:33.940 --> 14:38.712
Oh, no, you're on your own,
dude. Dog shit's not
my department. Hmm?

14:38.779 --> 14:42.849
If you were mayor, everything
would be a hell of a lot easier
to get done.

14:42.916 --> 14:46.452
Think of the possibilities.
Those zoning variances?
Just gone, good‐bye, adios.

14:46.520 --> 14:49.322
What, spend my time hangin' out
with a bunch of politicians?
No way, Doug.

14:49.389 --> 14:52.492
They're liars and crooks.
What about the mojo?

14:52.559 --> 14:54.460
[ Laughs ]

14:54.528 --> 14:57.197
Doug Rich, you're crazier than
a shithouse rat, you know that?

14:57.263 --> 15:00.366
A hundred and fifty
million dollar crazy.

15:03.504 --> 15:06.106
Hey,
how's it goin'?
[ Mutters ]

15:11.778 --> 15:14.480
Put this here?
Sure.

15:14.548 --> 15:18.552
Can I get winners?
All right, you're next.

15:20.220 --> 15:22.422
[ Cael ]
Oh.
Lucky shot, kid.

15:22.488 --> 15:26.627
Didn't think that was
gonna drop. Want a chance
to win your money back?

15:29.530 --> 15:31.998
[ Car Alarm Blaring
In Distance ]

15:41.407 --> 15:43.677
♪♪♪♪ [ Car Stereo:
Hip‐hop, Indistinct ]

15:49.015 --> 15:51.117
<i>[ Keys Jingle ]</i>

15:55.822 --> 15:57.824
[ Alarm Chirps,
Horn Honks ]

15:57.891 --> 16:00.026
[ <i>Men Chattering,</i>
<i>Laughing</i> ]

16:02.395 --> 16:04.565
Hey, we got
a little somethin'.

16:06.232 --> 16:08.168
Mmm!

16:09.402 --> 16:12.472
She's kinda sexy, dog.
[ Laughs ]

16:12.539 --> 16:15.576
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah.

16:19.145 --> 16:22.616
[ Sniffs ]
She smells good too.

16:22.683 --> 16:24.751
Not bad.
[ Laughs ]
Know what I'm sayin'?

16:24.818 --> 16:26.720
Yeah, uh‐huh.

16:34.194 --> 16:38.098
♪♪♪♪ [ Woman Singing,
Indistinct ]

16:38.164 --> 16:42.736
♪♪ Under a moon
like electric snow ♪♪

16:48.642 --> 16:53.479
♪♪ And it was there I confess
that we first had
a bed to share ♪♪

16:55.481 --> 16:57.784
[ Chattering ]

16:57.851 --> 17:00.086
Nice technique.

17:01.087 --> 17:03.223
These things'll kill ya.

17:05.290 --> 17:07.359
Might as well be free.

17:10.163 --> 17:12.898
Shh.
Lips are sealed.

17:12.965 --> 17:15.167
They look like they
can keep a secret.

17:15.234 --> 17:17.403
Keep a lot more
than that.

17:17.470 --> 17:20.641
[ Man ]
Anybody in this flea pit
know how to play nine ball?

17:20.707 --> 17:23.977
‐ [ Man #2 ]
Nah. Gonna take a pass.
‐ Ah, you know what?

17:24.044 --> 17:27.914
I gotta go take his money, so‐‐
I‐I'd really like
to buy you a beer.

17:27.981 --> 17:30.250
Do your thing.

17:34.621 --> 17:38.291
What are we playin'?
Texas express, one pushout?
What?

17:38.358 --> 17:42.395
You got any money, kid?
Or we have to wait
for your mama?

17:44.898 --> 17:49.069
I'm‐I'm sorry, I'm a little
hard of hearin'. Did you just
say you're kind of a dummy?

17:49.135 --> 17:51.471
[ Laughs ]
[ Laughs, Groans ]

17:51.538 --> 17:53.674
[ Man ]
Whoa!
[ Groans ]

17:55.208 --> 17:57.477
[ Men Chattering, Shouting ]

17:57.544 --> 18:00.246
Hey, where'd that
kid run off to?
<i>[ Man ] Cael?</i>

18:00.313 --> 18:03.817
Cael Malloy.
Get in here quick.

18:03.884 --> 18:07.120
‐ [ Man ]
Come on! Let's find him!
‐ Get in back.

18:07.187 --> 18:10.323
[ Man ]
You follow the trailer
along the side.

18:15.596 --> 18:18.064
I'm, uh,

18:18.131 --> 18:21.001
grateful to y'all
for the help back there.

18:21.067 --> 18:23.303
Looked like you
could use some help.

18:23.369 --> 18:27.340
‐ No shit.
‐ [ Chuckles ]

18:27.407 --> 18:30.611
Name's Declan Cassidy.
That's Caitlin behind the wheel.

18:30.677 --> 18:33.279
‐ Hi.
‐ Well, pleased to meet you.

18:33.346 --> 18:36.282
[ All Laughing ]

18:36.349 --> 18:39.252
No, Wayne.
I won't be home for a while.

18:39.319 --> 18:41.221
‐ But it's past 11:00.
‐ I'm double baggin'.

18:41.287 --> 18:45.759
Oh, you're double bagging.
Double bagging's when you go to
more than one meeting a day...

18:45.826 --> 18:48.695
because your life
is so goddamn stressful.

18:48.762 --> 18:53.333
‐ Right. Well, you just‐‐
You got‐‐ Well, okay, but‐‐
‐ Oh, shit.

18:53.399 --> 18:56.870
‐ Hello? [ Scoffs ] God.
‐ <i>[ Phone Clatters ]</i>

19:01.942 --> 19:04.477
You stalkin' me now?

19:04.545 --> 19:06.780
I check up on
all my clients.

19:06.847 --> 19:09.850
Oh, clients.
Is that what you call us?
Huh. Well, I tell you what.

19:09.916 --> 19:14.420
I'm doin' just great
here at the lovely
Rudy and Flo's Fish Shack.

19:14.487 --> 19:18.458
But I'm beat,
and I'm goin' home.

19:18.525 --> 19:21.361
Your place is downtown,
right?

19:21.427 --> 19:25.198
Yeah.
So, how you gettin' home?

19:25.265 --> 19:28.935
How, uh‐‐ I told you.
I take the bus.

19:29.002 --> 19:31.204
Which route?
14.

19:31.271 --> 19:33.774
Goes straight
past my place.

19:37.110 --> 19:39.112
[ Chattering ]
[ Siren Wailing ]

19:39.179 --> 19:42.949
How 'bout I give you
a ride home?

19:43.016 --> 19:47.287
No, that's okay. I mean,
I‐‐ I gotta go lock up
and stuff. I ain't‐‐

19:47.353 --> 19:49.790
Don't worry.
I'll lock up.
I'll‐‐ Okay.

20:00.701 --> 20:03.069
Curious as to how
you know my name.

20:03.136 --> 20:05.305
Word's out
you're on the road.

20:08.174 --> 20:11.311
Hmm. Used to work
for one of your cousins.
Kind of recognize you.

20:11.377 --> 20:14.781
[ Laughs ]
So where you headed,
Cael?

20:14.848 --> 20:17.518
‐ I'm just hittin' the road.
‐ Mm‐hmm.

20:17.584 --> 20:22.122
‐ You can ride with us.
‐ That's nice of you.

20:22.188 --> 20:25.592
‐ Think I'm gonna go solo
for a while though.
‐ As you like.

20:25.659 --> 20:28.094
[ Loudly ]
You okay back there, hon?

20:28.161 --> 20:30.296
Yeah, fine.

20:33.934 --> 20:35.869
This is Rosaleen.

20:35.936 --> 20:38.304
Hi.

20:39.205 --> 20:41.207
Hi, Rosaleen.

20:41.274 --> 20:43.977
[ Man, Woman Chattering ]

20:44.044 --> 20:46.613
Okay, uh, this is it.

20:46.680 --> 20:48.649
Um‐‐

20:48.715 --> 20:50.717
Uh, bathroom.

20:50.784 --> 20:55.455
And where we're standing
is the living room,
the kitchen and bedroom.

21:00.193 --> 21:03.029
[ Phone Buzzing ]
I'm just gonna go
to the bathroom.

21:04.998 --> 21:07.000
[ Door Closes ]

21:13.974 --> 21:15.876
Dahlia, where are you?

21:15.942 --> 21:18.011
[ Whispering ]
For God's sake,
would you stop calling me?

21:18.078 --> 21:20.146
‐ Why are you whispering?
‐ I'm at a meeting.

21:20.213 --> 21:24.017
What, you're still at a meeting?
I mean, it's midnight. What,
are you triple bagging now?

21:24.084 --> 21:28.154
Do not mock my sobriety, Wayne.
I'll get home soon.

21:28.221 --> 21:31.525
You don't trust me, huh?
You don't.

21:31.592 --> 21:35.295
‐ You don't trust me.
‐ [ Sighs ]

21:35.361 --> 21:39.600
You know what?
I'm working my ass off to get
my shit together, Wayne,

21:39.666 --> 21:43.504
and I will get home
when I goddamn get home!

21:48.575 --> 21:52.779
‐ You lose somethin'?
‐ Part of my job.

21:52.846 --> 21:55.481
Is there any part of my life
that ain't part of your job?

21:55.549 --> 21:59.853
As a matter of fact, no.

21:59.920 --> 22:02.989
Let's have
a real good look then, shall we?
Let's see what we got here.

22:03.056 --> 22:05.058
Oh. Oh, look.
Frying pan.

22:06.560 --> 22:08.829
Now‐‐ Oh, plates. Ooh!

22:08.895 --> 22:11.464
What? Silverware!

22:11.532 --> 22:13.900
Oh, my gosh,
what will we find next?

22:13.967 --> 22:17.938
Maybe what you're really
interested in is the kind
of sheets I got on my bed.

22:29.783 --> 22:32.352
[ Sighs ]

22:32.418 --> 22:34.588
I'm sorry.
I just got bad news.

22:34.655 --> 22:38.792
‐ Your son?
‐ Yeah. He didn't come home.

22:38.859 --> 22:43.096
‐ Sorry.
‐ It's my asshole
husband's fault.

22:43.163 --> 22:45.699
For every minute
you stay angry,

22:46.867 --> 22:50.203
you give up 60 seconds
of peace of mind.

22:50.270 --> 22:53.373
‐ That right?
‐ Mm‐hmm.

22:53.439 --> 22:57.611
‐ You make that up?
‐ No, read it somewhere.

22:57.678 --> 22:59.713
<i>But I think about it...</i>

22:59.780 --> 23:03.717
whenever my head takes my heart
to a place I don't want to be.

23:08.088 --> 23:09.990
[ Clears Throat ]

23:14.895 --> 23:16.763
Uhh‐‐

23:16.830 --> 23:21.835
<i>I, uh‐‐</i>
<i>[ Scoffs ] I gotta go.</i>

23:21.902 --> 23:24.170
Yeah.

23:25.438 --> 23:29.743
Well, thanks for stoppin' by.

23:51.565 --> 23:53.967
<i>Cael, it's Dad.</i>

23:54.034 --> 23:57.003
Look, I know you're
working some things out,

23:57.070 --> 24:00.907
and maybe... it's just not
a good time to be at home.

24:01.975 --> 24:07.514
But just‐‐ If‐‐
Look, call your mom. Okay?

24:07.581 --> 24:09.916
'Cause she's really worried.

24:13.019 --> 24:14.921
I love you, Cael.

24:20.861 --> 24:23.964
Oh, go home.

24:26.533 --> 24:28.468
[ Thudding ]

24:28.535 --> 24:30.571
[ Rustling ]

25:03.003 --> 25:04.971
[ Sighs ]

25:05.038 --> 25:06.873
[ Mutters ]

25:12.679 --> 25:15.348
Jesus Christ!
[ Sighs ]

25:15.415 --> 25:17.784
Sammi.

25:17.851 --> 25:20.353
Wha‐‐ What's the matter?
Where's Mom?

25:20.420 --> 25:23.524
She's, uh‐‐
She's working late.

25:23.590 --> 25:27.127
I saw someone outside.
What were they doing?

25:27.193 --> 25:30.196
He was sneaking around
and looking through the trash.

25:30.263 --> 25:32.933
He took the trash, Dad.
All of it.
All of it?

25:32.999 --> 25:36.136
‐ It's not a joke.
‐ I'll call Security, okay?

25:38.138 --> 25:40.741
[ Beeping ]
Dad.

25:40.807 --> 25:43.977
I found some blood
the other day
on the carpet.

25:44.044 --> 25:48.515
I cleaned it up.
I used a towel
to clean up the blood,

25:48.582 --> 25:50.751
and I put the towel
in the trash.

25:53.386 --> 25:56.189
You think that guy took it?

25:56.256 --> 26:01.628
You've been watching
too much CSI, haven't ya?
Hey, don't worry.

26:02.963 --> 26:05.666
I tell you what.
You go back to bed.
I'll be right in.

26:05.732 --> 26:07.968
Okay?
I'll just call these people.

26:08.034 --> 26:10.637
‐ [ Sighs ]
‐ [ Dale ]
What?

26:10.704 --> 26:15.208
It's me.
We've got a problem.
I know.
He's still at the motel.

26:19.913 --> 26:23.684
Jesus, Sammi.
[ Sighs ]
You still up?

26:23.750 --> 26:25.819
What were you
looking for?
Nothing.

26:25.886 --> 26:29.089
Well, uh‐‐ uh, a towel.

26:29.155 --> 26:31.324
You know,
to dry something up with.

26:34.728 --> 26:38.364
Sammi, you don't remember
which kind of towel you used
the other night, do you?

26:38.431 --> 26:41.334
To clean up the blood?
Yeah.

27:09.796 --> 27:14.134
We could steal it.
No, then he'd know it's gone.
Then we'll never get rid of him.

27:14.200 --> 27:17.237
‐ Oh, I'll get rid of him.
‐ Just do exactly what I say.

27:20.206 --> 27:23.343
[ Man #1 ] Call you up.
[ Man #2 ]
Come on, man. Open the door.

27:23.409 --> 27:26.112
That's the one I was
tellin' you about.
[ Thudding ]

27:26.179 --> 27:28.381
[ Dog Barking ]

27:28.448 --> 27:30.383
Oh, shit!

27:42.863 --> 27:44.998
[ Mouths Words ]

27:50.571 --> 27:53.840
‐ Hey. What's up, sweetie?
‐ You touch me,
I'm gonna kill you.

27:53.907 --> 27:56.476
‐ We'll see about that, bitch.
‐ I asked you real nicely.

27:56.543 --> 28:00.213
[ Grunting, Groaning ]
Yeah. Get her!

28:00.280 --> 28:03.416
[ Shouts ]
Ow! Ow!
Somebody grab her, man!

28:03.483 --> 28:05.819
‐ [ Siren Wailing ]
‐ Yo, let's go, man!
Let's go, man!

28:05.886 --> 28:09.289
‐ Get in!
‐ <i>Run, man!</i>

28:17.163 --> 28:19.900
Why are you stoppin'?
Why are y‐‐ Okay.

28:21.668 --> 28:25.138
Hey, go on, go.

28:25.205 --> 28:30.210
[ Shift Lever Clicks ]
What are‐‐ Whoa, man.

28:30.276 --> 28:34.447
I don't know what
I would have done
if you hadn't showed up.

28:34.515 --> 28:37.751
I shouldn't have taken
a walk this time of night,
you know?

28:37.818 --> 28:41.822
I guess I'll‐‐
I'll owe you one.
[ Cries ]

28:43.023 --> 28:47.193
[ Sobs, Sighs ]
Will you drive?
Now, come on.

28:47.260 --> 28:50.196
What, you're not
gonna say anything?
You're not gonna drive?

28:50.263 --> 28:52.666
Tell me what
I should do, Dahlia.
What you should do?

28:52.733 --> 28:56.069
You should get your friends,
go back, find those kids
and kick their goddamn asses!

28:56.136 --> 28:58.939
That's what you should do!
Tell me what
I should do with you.

28:59.005 --> 29:01.007
What do you mean?

29:01.074 --> 29:03.810
That car‐‐
Is it yours?
What car?

29:03.877 --> 29:06.647
That car!

29:06.713 --> 29:09.315
It's yours.
I saw you.

29:09.382 --> 29:11.918
What, you follow me now?
Is that,
or is that not your car?

29:11.985 --> 29:16.022
Yes! No! Jesus!
Uh, yeah, it's my car!

29:16.089 --> 29:19.359
If I ran the plates,
would that car
come out stolen, Dahlia?

29:19.425 --> 29:21.394
Sort of. Okay‐‐
Sort of?

29:21.461 --> 29:25.065
Why'd you park four blocks
from your place of work?
Maybe I like to walk!

29:25.131 --> 29:28.068
You're not living there!

29:28.134 --> 29:30.804
[ Shift Lever Clicks ]
What are you doin'?

29:30.871 --> 29:33.306
Give me one good reason
why I shouldn't take you in.
Oh, man.

29:33.373 --> 29:35.809
Right now!
'Cause I'm doin' my best!

29:35.876 --> 29:39.913
I am doin' my best, goddamn it!
I did everything
you said I should do.

29:39.980 --> 29:43.249
What can I do?
But you're lying to me.

29:43.316 --> 29:46.286
Okay, I'm lyin' a little bit!
I am lyin' a little bit,
but I'm tryin'.

29:46.352 --> 29:49.489
Okay, please, because‐‐
Don't send me back.
Please, for my kids.

29:49.556 --> 29:53.493
Oh, shut up about your kids.
Look, I went out on
a limb for you!

29:53.560 --> 29:57.397
Look, I'm not gonna see 'em
again if you take me back.
I'm not gonna see my kids again.

29:57.463 --> 30:01.034
Please, please, please.
I'll do anything.
I'll do anything you want.

30:01.101 --> 30:03.904
What do you want me to do?
I'll do anything right now.

30:03.970 --> 30:06.139
Right here. Come on.
I'll do anything.

30:08.909 --> 30:12.412
[ Man In Distance ]
Yes, ma'am. I'll put those here.
All right?

30:12.478 --> 30:14.314
[ Scoffs ]

30:34.768 --> 30:37.270
Get out of my car.
You son of a bi‐‐

30:37.337 --> 30:40.941
I just got jacked.
I just got jacked!

30:41.007 --> 30:43.677
What about my‐‐
Get out of
my goddamn car!

30:43.744 --> 30:46.346
Okay. What about my parole?
What are you gonna do about
my parole?

30:46.412 --> 30:49.916
We're done.
[ Panting, Sighing ]

31:09.469 --> 31:11.905
[ Rosaleen ]
Travellers all over are telling
stories about the Malloys.

31:11.972 --> 31:14.875
You're the James Gang
or somethin'.
[ Laughs ]

31:14.941 --> 31:20.647
Say you've been livin' in one
of them fancy gated communities.

31:22.482 --> 31:25.619
Better than livin'
in a trailer, huh?

31:26.687 --> 31:28.589
Not so much.

31:28.655 --> 31:30.857
Whole lotta people
worryin' about their stuff,

31:30.924 --> 31:33.694
how to stop people
from taking their stuff,

31:33.760 --> 31:36.229
or... how to get more stuff.

31:37.698 --> 31:39.600
All about stuff.

31:41.935 --> 31:44.104
Too much stuff
if you ask me.

31:45.572 --> 31:49.810
What about you?
Plan on stayin' on the road
with your folks?

31:49.876 --> 31:54.781
Oh, D‐‐ Declan and Caitlin,
they're not my folks.
They're my in‐laws.

31:54.848 --> 31:57.017
‐ You're married?
‐ Was.

31:57.083 --> 32:00.420
Uh, Bryan, my husband,

32:02.055 --> 32:04.257
died from a fall.

32:04.324 --> 32:06.259
I'm sorry.

32:06.326 --> 32:09.329
Mmm. It was his
own stupid fault.

32:09.395 --> 32:11.532
He was drunk.

32:11.598 --> 32:14.134
That was three years ago.

32:14.200 --> 32:16.436
I've been with
these guys ever since.
[ Clears Throat ]

32:18.505 --> 32:23.143
‐ So, gonna hit the road, Cael.
‐ I might jump out then.

32:25.045 --> 32:27.147
Well, suit yourself.

32:28.214 --> 32:30.951
Hey, stick with us, Cael.

32:35.155 --> 32:37.724
I‐‐ I'd like it if you did.

32:40.827 --> 32:42.596
Ain't like Texas
is goin' anywhere.

32:47.033 --> 32:49.469
Attaboy.

32:49.536 --> 32:53.874
What's the plan, Wayne?
I am under as much pressure
as you are here.

32:53.940 --> 32:56.743
I know you have all
the answers, but there's
a big difference...

32:56.810 --> 32:59.513
between the towel
in that room and the towel
that you're holdin'.

32:59.580 --> 33:02.583
‐ There's no blood, Wayne.
‐ [ Clicks ]

33:06.553 --> 33:09.656
[ Groaning ]

33:09.723 --> 33:11.224
‐ Dad.
‐ Oh, shit.

33:11.291 --> 33:14.427
Sam.
What are you doing?

33:14.494 --> 33:17.363
I'm gonna go
take care of the phone.

33:19.499 --> 33:21.802
‐ What are you doing?
‐ Are we in trouble, Dad?

33:21.868 --> 33:25.171
There's a man in that motel room
who could make things
really difficult for us.

33:25.238 --> 33:29.342
He's looking for Pete?
And he's convinced himself
that we know where he is.

33:32.045 --> 33:35.348
He could kill the dream,
Sammi.

33:37.918 --> 33:41.154
Why are you working
with Dale, Dad?

33:41.221 --> 33:43.389
‐ [ Wayne Scoffs ]
‐ I thought he was the enemy.

33:43.456 --> 33:47.093
Well‐‐
Is that Pete's blood
on the towel?

33:49.896 --> 33:52.332
Life is complicated, Sam.

33:52.398 --> 33:54.968
I thought life
was a river.

33:55.035 --> 33:57.437
Yeah, it's that too.

33:57.504 --> 33:59.840
Hi, my name
is Pete Mincey.
[ Man ] Uh‐huh.

33:59.906 --> 34:01.808
I'm trying to reach
Chet Landry.

34:01.875 --> 34:06.913
He called me, and I think
his room phone is broken, so‐‐
All right.

34:06.980 --> 34:10.382
I don't have
his cell phone number.
Could you‐‐ Thanks.

34:13.085 --> 34:17.322
Okay, now stay here.
I'll be right back.

34:27.833 --> 34:29.536
Dad.
Get outta here!

34:29.603 --> 34:32.038
I want to come.
I can look out.
No, absolutely not.

34:32.105 --> 34:36.543
It's my fault.
All right, you're on lookout.
Anything goes wrong, you run!

34:38.277 --> 34:42.683
[ Imitates Static ]
I was‐‐ [ Imitates Static ]

34:44.184 --> 34:45.886
[ Grunts ]

34:45.952 --> 34:48.822
[ TV: Indistinct ]

34:52.391 --> 34:54.527
[ Imitates Static ]
Could you‐‐
[ Imitates Static ]

34:54.594 --> 34:56.462
That‐‐

35:24.925 --> 35:26.993
[ Cell Phone Rings ]

35:27.060 --> 35:28.929
Dahlia?

35:28.995 --> 35:32.065
Dahlia? Who's Dahlia?
Doug Rich!

35:32.132 --> 35:35.335
You dog.
Who's Dahlia?

35:36.670 --> 35:39.172
You do‐‐ Oh, no, no, no.
Don't hang up.
Don't hang up.

35:39.239 --> 35:42.075
I got somethin' big to tell you,
somethin' really big.
You know how‐‐ Hey!

35:42.142 --> 35:46.279
Don't hang up. You know how‐‐
You know how Bush calls
Karl Rove "Turd Blossom"?

35:46.346 --> 35:49.783
<i>Huh? Well, you're gonna be</i>
<i>my Turd Blossom, Doug.</i>

35:49.850 --> 35:53.219
I'm runnin' for mayor,
and you're gonna make sure
I win.

35:53.286 --> 35:56.757
All right?
Who's got mojo now?
Huh?

35:56.823 --> 36:01.261
Turd Blossom!
Oh, yeah, Gi Gi
and I are back.

36:01.327 --> 36:03.897
[ Chuckles ]
See, I told you I'd do it.

36:16.910 --> 36:19.379
[ Wayne ]
Sammi?

36:21.081 --> 36:23.650
Sammi! Sammi.

36:26.987 --> 36:29.255
[ Whispers ]
Oh, my God.
Get back. Get back!

36:32.325 --> 36:34.561
Sammi, get back.
Get back!

36:44.337 --> 36:47.541
Oh, hey, brother. Uh, I think
you are entering my room.
Hey, whoa, bub.

36:47.608 --> 36:50.176
Hey, buddy.
This is my‐‐ This is my room.
<i>It's my room.</i>

36:50.243 --> 36:53.680
I hate to be the bearer
of bad news, but I paid
good money for this room.

36:53.747 --> 36:56.349
Hey, you know, you're drunk.
Back off, buddy.
Oh, don't touch me.

36:56.416 --> 36:58.719
Don't you touch me!
Don't touch me!
Back off, buddy!

36:58.785 --> 37:01.421
You touch a guy.
Now, what is that?

37:01.487 --> 37:05.058
‐ That's inappropriate
behavior... right there.
‐ Hey, you're drunk.

37:05.125 --> 37:08.061
It is my personal space
here, man.
<i>Hey, you're drunk.</i>

37:08.128 --> 37:10.864
My personal space.
Know what I'm sayin'?
Yeah, I know what you're sayin'.

37:10.931 --> 37:14.334
All right. You know what?
I do believe...

37:14.400 --> 37:17.370
I am stayin' at the room
across the street.

37:17.437 --> 37:20.841
I wouldn't stay at this shithole
if you offered me free porn
and a continental breakfast.

37:20.907 --> 37:23.409
Well, move it
along then, bud.
Hmm.

37:24.778 --> 37:27.313
Hmm.

37:29.182 --> 37:31.417
[ Chattering In Distance ]

37:52.372 --> 37:54.775
‐ What are we doin' here?
‐ We're bunkin' down
here tonight.

37:54.841 --> 37:57.678
Come on.
Let's get you somethin' to eat.

37:57.744 --> 37:59.880
<i>Well, come on.</i>
<i>Ain't you hungry?</i>

38:03.950 --> 38:05.952
Who's that?

38:06.019 --> 38:08.021
Eamon Quinn.

38:09.122 --> 38:11.157
No shit.

38:11.224 --> 38:13.827
Come on. Let's go get
somethin' to eat.

38:13.894 --> 38:16.062
Come on.

38:16.129 --> 38:18.131
All right.

38:18.198 --> 38:20.200
[ Chattering ]

38:20.266 --> 38:22.368
Uh‐huh. Yeah, he did.

38:24.437 --> 38:26.907
[ Woman ]
Hey, talk to Mark.
He'll help you.

38:31.678 --> 38:34.414
That was close.
Oh, that was too close.

38:36.583 --> 38:39.553
We got the towel though.
Yeah, we got the towel.

38:40.921 --> 38:44.958
You're good.
I mean, you're CSI good.

38:45.025 --> 38:47.928
Hey.
Thank you.

38:50.897 --> 38:54.935
‐ What are you doin' up?
‐ We're having
a father‐son moment.

38:56.503 --> 38:59.072
‐ You okay?
‐ Sure.
I'm gonna make some tea.

39:00.741 --> 39:02.609
Hey, Dad.

39:02.676 --> 39:04.978
Yeah?
You gonna tell Mom
about the motel?

39:05.045 --> 39:08.448
Let's keep that between
you and me‐‐ for the moment.
Okay?

39:08.515 --> 39:11.718
‐ Okay, you get some sleep.
‐ Dad?

39:11.785 --> 39:14.988
Yeah?
Thanks for not
abandoning me back there.

39:16.356 --> 39:18.892
Hey.
That will never happen.

39:18.959 --> 39:23.429
Okay? I will never
abandon you... ever.

39:25.666 --> 39:28.468
I know, Dad.
I trust you.

39:29.970 --> 39:31.872
Okay, that's good.

39:37.210 --> 39:39.079
<i>[ Cell Phone Ringing ]</i>

39:40.514 --> 39:42.916
‐ Dale?
‐ P.I. is gone.

39:42.983 --> 39:45.251
You saw him go?
Followed him
out of town.

39:45.318 --> 39:49.222
‐ [ Teakettle Whistles ]
‐ Well, let's hope that's
the last we hear from him.

39:49.289 --> 39:51.391
See you around the office,
partner.

39:51.457 --> 39:53.326
[ Beeps ]
Okay.

39:53.393 --> 39:55.896
You hear from Cael?

40:04.571 --> 40:07.808
‐ Where were you last night?
‐ I slept in the car.

40:07.874 --> 40:11.845
Wouldn't start
this mornin'.
So how did you get home?

40:11.912 --> 40:13.747
Walked.

40:15.916 --> 40:19.119
We have to find Cael,
so let's start by calling
everyone he knows.

40:19.185 --> 40:22.022
He's on the road, Wayne.
Di Di told me.
Oh.

40:22.088 --> 40:25.158
No one's seen him.
Well, we'll give him
till tomorrow.

40:25.225 --> 40:27.193
Yeah?
And then what?

40:27.260 --> 40:30.430
I tell you. I'm gonna kick
his sorry little ass
when I see him.

40:30.496 --> 40:32.533
He ain't gonna be able
to sit down for a week.

40:32.599 --> 40:36.036
So you slept in the car?
Yeah. It really hurt yesterday
when you called me a liar.

40:36.102 --> 40:38.539
I didn't call you a liar.
You said
you didn't trust me.

40:38.605 --> 40:41.942
I was worried out of my mind
about Cael, the way you are.
Oh, all right.

40:42.008 --> 40:44.210
You know, I didn't know
where you were.
Okay.

40:47.614 --> 40:51.217
[ Sighs ]
Okay, you're not a liar.

40:51.284 --> 40:53.887
No, I'm not a liar.
No.

40:53.954 --> 40:56.056
I'm sorry.

40:57.624 --> 40:59.926
Hey, I trust you.

41:00.994 --> 41:03.196
Come on.

41:10.003 --> 41:12.205
Get some sleep.
